# Python
.venv/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pytest_tmp*/
# Build / packaging artifacts
build/
dist/
*.egg-info/
sbom*.json
# IDE
.idea/
# Runtime / logs (regenerated)
# 2026-07-10 audit finding: patterns with a MIDDLE slash (.agents/logs/, .agents/reports/) are
# anchored to the repo root by git's own gitignore rules and do NOT match at other depths --
# confirmed empirically (a nested core/.agents/logs/ was NOT caught by the unprefixed pattern).
# Several LOG_DIR definitions across core/ resolve via os.getcwd() (not a fixed repo-root
# anchor), so running any of them from a non-root cwd can write the real audit chain (real
# approver identities, real plan hashes) to a nested, non-ignored path. runs/ and artifacts/
# (trailing slash only, no middle slash) already match at any depth by git's own glob rules --
# confirmed via git check-ignore against a real nested core/runs/ -- so only the two below
# needed the **/ prefix to close the gap. core/.agents/cache/ (AWS Price List dimension-name
# cache, non-sensitive, but the same cwd quirk) added as its own entry for the same reason.
**/.agents/logs/
**/.agents/reports/
**/.agents/cache/
artifacts/
runs/
# Ad hoc session pytest-summary logs at repo root (bare pass/fail counts, no paths or
# identifiers -- still shouldn't be committed as permanent clutter)
pt_*.log
# Terraform
*.tfstate
*.tfstate.*
.terraform/
.terraform.lock.hcl
tfplan
# Credentials / one-shot tokens (must never be committed)
*.token
.minus_tf/

# Client-specific backend config (never commit)
backend.hcl

# vendor-owned diagram icons — local only, never committed (see docs/architecture_svg_spec.md v3)
assets/architecture-icons/

# generated repo-structure snapshot — a point-in-time reference, not maintained documentation;
# would go stale in source control, so it's local-only (regenerate on demand instead)
docs/REPO_MAP.md
